cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI 

This paper is about interpreting and improving natural language processing in machines using brain imaging recordings of subjects reading complex natural text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which suggests the possibility of it being in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of different NLP models, which could place it in cs.LG (Learning). The use of brain imaging recordings could also suggest cs.CV (Computer Vision) as a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the interaction between NLP and cognitive neuroscience, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
